Class Colors.Obj

java.lang.Object
color.Colors.Obj
All Implemented Interfaces:
Category.Object<Color>
Enclosing class:
Colors
public class Colors.Obj extends Object implements Category.Object<Color>
Implementation of interface Category's generic interface Category.Object.  Objects are the elements of the category.  If the category is viewed as a directed graph, they correspond to the nodes.  Both in Java and in category theory, objects are members of a collection.  In Java, it is the collection of values associated to a class.

    • getIdentity

      public Colors.Morph getIdentity()
      Returns the morphism identity on this object. For every object A there is an arrow which is a unit of composition.  This arrow loops from the object to itself.  Being a unit of composition means that, when composed with any arrow that either starts at A or ends at A, respectively, it gives back the same arrow.  The unit arrow for object A is called identity on A.
      Specified by:
